{
  "stem": "26728.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But-- I mean, they were in a, they were about this big, and they were in a jar, like a gallon jar, a jug, a gallon jug, with alcohol.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they had long hair and beards.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't know what the hell they were, but they were human heads.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I've read about them since.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there's a lot of controversy about what these-- some of the deniers say that these were borrowed from a museum.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, you know, how do they know where they came from?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Uh, that's one of the things I love to do is argue with revisionists and deniers on the internet.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because, you know, it's pretty hard to shoot a guy down, when he-- when I'm dealing with a 35-year-old man who only has read books, and-- anti-Holocaust books, anti-Semitic books, pro-Nazi books.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As opposed to someone who has not only been there, but now I have about a hundred books that I have read.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I've read every book in the library, the Eugene library, about the Holocaust that they have, since 1992.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now I'm-- I feel qualified to debate with, and I challenged.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't mean this to sound to be bragging.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have challenged Holocaust deniers to publicly debate me on television.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And nobody has accepted the bait.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Right here in Eugene.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, I'd kick ass and they know it, if you'll pardon the expression.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My army slang is coming back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Uh, that-- OK, I went back to the-- to the organ room, and went through that same emotional feeling that I had before.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That this is just-- the bodies out there were not as-- [PAUSES] as depressing to me, as the fact that these had been living human beings that had been experimented with one way or another.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
